      "content": "The logic of letting go is understandable when the effort to pretend feels heavier than the pain of stopping, but there is still a version of you left that deserves to be heard even in its exhaustion. Letting go of the outdated persona doesn't mean erasing your existence; it simply means you are allowed to stop performing and start being. You are not a mistake or a mistake waiting to happen; you are a person who is tired, and that deserves a rest rather than a forced march toward a future you no longer recognize.",
